components.content: Click the events to put them in order from 1 to 4.
You can click them again to undo.
Young elephants see older elephant run away from bees.
Older elephant gets stung by bee.
Young elephants learn to be scared of bee buzzing.
Older elephant learns to be scared of bee buzzing.
Try again by clicking the Reset button.
An older elephant has to get stung first to learn to be scared of the buzzing. Older elephants then teach the younger elephants. The correct order is:
Older elephant gets stung by bee.
Older elephant learns to be scared of bee buzzing.
Young elephants see older elephant run away from bees.
Young elephants learn to be scared of bee buzzing.

Correct! An older elephant has to get stung by a bee first to then learn to be scared of their buzzing sound.
After an older elephant has learned something, it can then teach it to the younger elephants.
